title: Earnings edition: Your first trade for Thursday
text:
Fast Money Final Trade: NFLX, BA & more
The Fast Money traders share their final trades of the day.
The " Fast Money " traders revealed which companies they're watching as earnings season gains momentum.
Dan Nathan had Boeing on his radar.
Steve Grasso was looking at Mobileye .
Karen Finerman liked Alphabet .
Guy Adami was bullish on Netflix even though the stock plummeted during extended trading.
Trader disclosure: On October 14, 2015, the following stocks and commodities mentioned or intended to be mentioned on CNBC's "Fast Money" were owned by the "Fast Money" traders: Dan Nathan is long PYPL Oct call calendar, BA Oct put spread, INTC Dec put spread, QQQ Oct put spread, UAL Oct/Nov put spread, XLF Dec put spread, XLF puts, XLP Nov calls, XLU call spread, TWTR. Steve Grasso is long AAPL, BA, BAC, CC, DD, DIS, DECK, EVGN, FIT, KBH, MJNA, MU, OLN, PFE, PHM, T, TWTR, GDX firm is long MCD, AMZN, SHLD kids own EFA, EFG, EWJ, IJR, SPY. Karen Finerman is long BAC, C, FINL, FL, GOOG, GOOGL, JPM, KORS, KORS call spreads, M, URI, she is short SPY, Her firm is long ANTM, AAPL, BAC, C, DIS, FINL, FL, GOOG, GOOGL, GPS, JPM, KORS, KORS call spreads, M, M calls, M call spreads, M long puts, SUNE, SUNE call spreads, URI, URI long puts, her firm is short IWM, SPY, MDY, USO, XRT, Karen Finerman is on the board of GrafTech International.Guy Adami is long CELG, EXAS, GS, INTC, Guy Adami's wife, Linda Snow, works at Merck.
